## Commands

```bash
bun run dev              # dev server
bun run build            # production build (runs prebuild image optimizer first)
bun run preview          # preview production build
bun run check            # TypeScript / svelte-check
bun run images:optimize  # run image prebuild pipeline manually (idempotent)
bun run check:seo        # validate SEO config and route registry
bun run validate         # run check + images:optimize + build + check:seo in sequence
bun run lint             # ESLint
bun run format           # Prettier
```

## Package manager — Bun only

This project uses **Bun**. Never substitute npm, npx, pnpm, or yarn.

```bash
bun install              # install dependencies (use --frozen-lockfile in CI)
bun add <pkg>            # add a package
bun run <script>         # run a script from package.json
```

**Never commit:** `node_modules/`, `.svelte-kit/`, `build/`, `dist/`, `.env`, `.env.*`, `bun.lockb`
**Always commit:** `bun.lock` (text lockfile — tracks exact dependency versions)

## Semantic HTML contract

Full reference: `docs/design-system/semantic-html-guide.md`
LLM rules (concise): `docs/design-system/llm-html-rules.md`

Before generating any HTML or Svelte components:

1. Use `Section.svelte` (`src/lib/components/Section.svelte`) for thematic page sections.
2. Use the most specific semantic element — `<article>`, `<nav>`, `<aside>`, `<figure>`, `<time>`, etc.
3. One `<main id="main-content">` per page — it lives in `+layout.svelte`. Never add a second.
4. One `<h1>` per page — the page title. Never put it in the site header.
5. Meaningful images: `<figure><img src="..." alt="..."></figure>`. Not CSS `background-image`.
6. Dates: `<time datetime="2026-04-26">April 26, 2026</time>`.
7. Links navigate (`<a href>`). Actions fire (`<button type="button">`).
8. Run the pre-generation checklist in `llm-html-rules.md` before finalizing.

The styleguide at `/styleguide` (dev only) shows live examples. Delete `src/routes/styleguide/` before going live.

## CSS and design system

Full rules: `docs/design-system/llm-css-rules.md` — paste that file's content below when working on CSS.

Quick rules:
- Edit `tokens.css` to change colors, fonts, spacing, and shape. That file is the brand file.
- Architecture files (`reset.css`, `base.css`, `animations.css`, `utilities.css`, `forms.css`) must not be edited for project-specific work except in the marked `BRAND-SPECIFIC` section at the bottom of each file.
- Reference semantic tokens (`var(--surface-raised)`) in component CSS — never raw oklch/hex values.
- Use `color-mix(in oklch, color X%, transparent)` for translucency. Never `opacity` on surfaces.
- This is a scrolling website. Do not add `html, body { overflow: hidden }`.
- Do not disable user zoom in `app.html`.

